File: About 250 men and boys across South Africa are expected to take part. eNCA/Zaid Harris JOHANNESBURG - Parliament has set aside two days for a National Men's Parliament event starting on Thursday. About 250 men and boys across South Africa are expected to take part. READ: The roles of men and women in unmaking misogyny in South Africa The event is meant to encourage men to be agents of social change to prevent gender-based violence, femicide, and the spread of HIV. The first day of the event coincides with International Men's Day.